Uses of Package
avahi4j

Packages that use avahi4j
avahi4j This is Avahi4J's main package which contains the classes to interact with Avahi. 
avahi4j.examples This package contains sample applications demonstrating how to use Avahi4J. 
 

Classes in avahi4j used by avahi4j
Address
          This class encapsulate an IP address, either IPv4 or IPv6.
Avahi4JConstants.BrowserEvent
          This enumeration contains a list of possible browser events (either from ServiceBrowser or RecordBrowser).
Avahi4JConstants.DNS_Class
          This enumeration contains a list of possible DNS classes
Avahi4JConstants.DNS_RRType
          This enumeration contains a list of possible DNS Resource Record types.
Avahi4JConstants.Protocol
          This enumeration lists supported procotols.
Client.State
          This enumeration lists the possible states of a client.
EntryGroup
          An entry group is used to publish new services, and to update existing ones.
EntryGroup.State
          This enumeration represents the various states an entry group can be in.
IClientCallback
          Classes implementing this interface can be notified when the state of a Client changes.
IEntryGroupCallback
          Classes implementing this interface are notified when the state of an EntryGroup changes.
IRecordBrowserCallback
          Classes implementing this interface receive notifications from RecordBrowser objects when records for a given host have been retrieved.
IServiceBrowserCallback
          Objects implementing this interface can receive notifications from a ServiceBrowser about services matching a set of criteria (given to the service browser when instantiated).
IServiceResolverCallback
          Classes implementing this interface receive notifications from ServiceResolver objects when a service (as registered with the service resovler object) has been resolved.
RecordBrowser
          Objects of this class are used to browse DNS records for a specific host.
ResolvedService
          This class encapsulates the details about a resolved service.
ServiceBrowser
          A service browser object can be used to look for services matching a given set of criteria.
ServiceResolver
          Objects of this class are used to resolve a service.
To create a service resolver object for a given service, call createServiceResolver() on an existing Client object.
ServiceResolver.ServiceResolverEvent
          This enumeration lists the possible resolver events.
